  "observations": [
    "Observations:",
    "1. I was surprised that NC119 lost voters over the past two years.",
    "2. In total the Ds lost 1%, the Rs no change, the Us gained 1%",
    "3. It is possible - though not conclusive - the Ds, by percentage, moved to the Us.",
    "4. Although the D losses were almost tripple the R losses, the percentages of D to R has not changed significantly. It is possible that some Rs moved to Us also.",
    "Conclusion:",
    "1. It is still clear to me that the election will be won or lost in the middle.",
    "2. All messaging must be directed to the middle's concerns.",
    "3. Ds will vote for Mark with middle messaging",
    "4. I don't believe that hot button social issues are winners. Many in the middle can lean either way.",
    "Who in in the middle? On indicator is to know how many Uaffs took Demballots in the primary. When I worked phones and post cards in Sam Edney's past runk I was given those Unaffs who did that. I talked to a number. The party should be able to deliver this information again. It is extremely important targeting information.",
    "Observations and Conclusions about 2026 Primary vs 2024 General NC 119 Results: (This data can't be a direct comparison between election years and type, but I believesome  conclusions can still be drawn.)",
    "Observations:",
    "The closeness of '26 vs '24 at this juncture is obvious. The question is, will it carry over to the General?",
    "Conclusions:",
    "1. Mark can win this district, but it will  be a tight race.",
    "2. All Democrats must turn out.",
    "3. Messaging must be to the middle to convenice them to vote Democrat."
  ]
}